Package org.zaproxy.zap.spider.filters

Class ParseFilter

java.lang.Object
org.zaproxy.zap.spider.filters.ParseFilter
Direct Known Subclasses:
DefaultParseFilter, MaxChildrenParseFilter
@Deprecated public abstract class ParseFilter extends Object
Deprecated.
(2.12.0) See the spider add-on in zap-extensions instead.
A ParseFilter is used to filter which resources should be parsed by the Spider after they have already been fetched and which shouldn't.

    • filtered

      public ParseFilter.FilterResult filtered(HttpMessage responseMessage)
      Deprecated.
      Tells whether or not the given resource is filtered. Filtered resources are not parsed.

      Default is not filtered.

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      the filter result, must not be null.
